# D365 F&O Extensibility

Microsoft source: [Method wrapping / CoC](https://learn.microsoft.com/dynamics365/fin-ops-core/dev-itpro/extensibility/method-wrapping-coc)

## Core rules

- `next` **unconditional at first level** — not inside if/while/for
- Wrapper signature matches base — no default param values in wrapper
- `[ExtensionOf(classStr(...))] final class MyPub_X_Extension`
- Separate extension class per form datasource/control CoC
- Prefer **CoC over delegates** when extracted methods exist (PU 7.3+)
- Event handlers: additive only — never unconditionally set `EventHandlerResult`

## Scenarios and recommendations

### Extend table validation (`validateWrite`, `validateInsert`)

**Recommend:** CoC on table methods via `[ExtensionOf(tableStr(...))]`; call `next` first, then apply custom rules.

**Avoid:** Overlay table; validate only in form without table CoC (bypasses non-UI callers).

### Extend form behavior (init, clicked, datasource events)

**Recommend:** Form extension for controls; **separate** `[ExtensionOf(formDataSourceStr(...))]` / `[ExtensionOf(formControlStr(...))]` classes for CoC.

**Avoid:** One monolithic extension class for all datasources; inline control code duplicating CoC structure.

### Side effect after insert/update (audit, sync)

**Recommend:** CoC on `insert`/`update` if wrappable; else Pre/Post **event handler** that does not block base unless business requires it.

**Avoid:** `doInsert`/`doUpdate`; setting `EventHandlerResult` unconditionally in Pre handlers.

### Replace branching logic (switch on enum/type)

**Recommend:** Extract default to `[Replaceable]` method; extend via CoC on replaceable method.

**Avoid:** Large switch with `default: throw` in a method others need to extend.

### Static helpers on standard types

**Recommend:** Static class `MyPub_CustTable_Extension` with target type as first parameter — utility only.

**Avoid:** Static extensions that hold state or replace instance behavior.

## CoC example

```xpp
// BAD — conditional next
public boolean validateWrite()
{
    if (this.MyField) { ret = next validateWrite(); }
    return ret;
}

// GOOD
public boolean validateWrite()
{
    boolean ret = next validateWrite();
    if (ret && this.MyField) { ret = this.validateCustomRule(); }
    return ret;
}
```

